#REMARK EXPERIMENTAL CONDITIONS
EXPERIMENTAL_DETAILS	FPLC-SAXS experiment was performed with Superdex-200 size-exclusion column. A 120 ul of the M-PTC at 10.9 mg/ml was applied to the column with a flow rate of 0.08 ml/min. The first 100 images (1sec exposure) were scaled and averaged to create a buffer-scattering profile, which was then subtracted from each of the subsequent images to produce the final scattering curve for each exposure. The program PRIMUS was employed to investigate concentration-dependent intermolecular interactions and to merge curves. The resulting SAXS prifile was not calibrated to absolute scale. Mw cannot be estimated by I(0) because of FPLC-SAXS experiment.
